## 9. Checklists

### Pre-Development

- [ ] Failure scenarios reasoned through (downstream down, empty data, concurrent writes, malformed input)?
- [ ] Failing test case written (TDD Red phase)?
- [ ] Connection pool type confirmed (`NullPool` for SQLite, `QueuePool` for Postgres)?
- [ ] ID generation uses database-native sequences?
- [ ] Pydantic/Zod schemas defined with strict types for all inputs?
- [ ] Operation is idempotent or has an idempotency key?
- [ ] Schema changes use migration tool, not raw DDL?
- [ ] Is this the simplest design that handles the known edge cases?

### Implementation

- [ ] Every `try/except` catches the narrowest type, logs with context, and re-raises or returns a structured error?
- [ ] Multi-step writes wrapped in a context-managed transaction?
- [ ] Null-safe access on all optional relationships and foreign keys?
- [ ] Every external call has an explicit timeout and retry strategy for transient failures?
- [ ] Zero hardcoded paths, secrets, or magic strings (use `settings` / `.env` / `Enum`)?
- [ ] All imports at top of file?
- [ ] Type hints on all function signatures?
- [ ] Paginated endpoints fetch all pages on the client, serve bounded pages on the server?
- [ ] All authenticated calls include auth headers?
- [ ] No mutable default arguments?
- [ ] No raw ORM models returned to clients (use response DTOs)?
- [ ] No SQL built with f-strings (use parameterized queries)?
- [ ] No blocking I/O in async functions?
- [ ] No secrets logged?
- [ ] No code duplication (searched codebase for existing helpers)?
- [ ] Frontend handles `isLoading`, `isError`, and `isEmpty`?

### Verification

- [ ] `rg "MAX\(id|StaticPool" ./app` returns zero results?
- [ ] `pip-audit` returns zero known vulnerabilities (or documented risk acceptance with mitigation)?
- [ ] Backend passes `mypy --strict` / Frontend passes `tsc --noEmit`?
- [ ] Zero violations from `ruff` (backend) / `eslint` (frontend)?
- [ ] Endpoint survives `hey -n 100 -c 10` without 500s or deadlocks?
- [ ] Edge cases tested (empty, null, duplicate, boundary, concurrent)?
- [ ] Existing test suite still passes?
- [ ] No DEBUG print statements remain?
- [ ] `/health` endpoint verifies all dependencies?
- [ ] Read the diff one more time -- is there anything left to simplify?

### Code Review

- [ ] No manual ID generation (`MAX(id) + 1`)
- [ ] No wrong pool type (`StaticPool` for SQLite)
- [ ] No hardcoded paths, secrets, or configuration
- [ ] No silent exception handling (`except: pass`, `except Exception: return None`)
- [ ] No missing input validation at the boundary
- [ ] No missing timeouts on external calls
- [ ] No missing transaction boundaries
- [ ] No missing null checks before attribute access
- [ ] No raw database models returned to clients
- [ ] No SQL injection vectors (f-string SQL)
- [ ] No blocking I/O in async code paths
- [ ] No mutable default arguments
- [ ] No secrets or PII in logs
- [ ] No unnecessary complexity or premature abstraction

